<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407146>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 32. Nothoodes taprobanae Andrewes, 1923, female paratype. A: habitus, with left antennomeres 6–11 attached to separate cardboard; B: mentum; C: prosternal process; D: left metepisternum and metacoxa (arrow shows lateral end of metacoxal basal sulcus); E: spermathecal complex and gonocoxites, ventral view. Scale lines = 2 mm (Fig. A); = 0.5 mm (Figs B–E)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4407146/files/figure.png" .

